Implemented the ambiguity-policy repair for `hybrid->frame` and `temporal->frame` in the compiler ambiguity lane.

- Added deterministic fallback family ranking (softmax over `SpaCyModalDecoder.family_logits`) when cue-count ranking is empty, and used it to still run adaptive ambiguity detection: [compiler.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-vector-5scope-1h-20260518T191418Z-codex-compiler_ambiguity/worktrees/agent-codex-compiler_ambiguity-packet-000375-20260518_200847/ipfs_datasets_py/logic/modal/compiler.py:272), [compiler.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-vector-5scope-1h-20260518T191418Z-codex-compiler_ambiguity/worktrees/agent-codex-compiler_ambiguity-packet-000375-20260518_200847/ipfs_datasets_py/logic/modal/compiler.py:547), [compiler.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-vector-5scope-1h-20260518T191418Z-codex-compiler_ambiguity/worktrees/agent-codex-compiler_ambiguity-packet-000375-20260518_200847/ipfs_datasets_py/logic/modal/compiler.py:124).
- Marked `hybrid->frame` as a priority signal-free adaptive pair (so zero-margin ties are treated as explicit outvoted ambiguity): [modal_registry.py](/home/barberb/portland-laws.github.io/workspace/codex-work/uscode-modal-vector-5scope-1h-20260518T191418Z-codex-compiler_ambiguity/worktrees/agent-codex-compiler_ambiguity-packet-000375-20260518_200847/ipfs_datasets_py/optimizers/logic_theorem_optimizer/modal_registry.py:64).
